-- ComplexNumber/exponential_imaginary.math
--
-- The exponential on the imaginary axis, coordinate by coordinate. The
-- number i·x (x real) has coordinates (0, x), so its powers follow the
-- recurrence
--   re((ix)^{k+1}) = −x·im((ix)^k),   im((ix)^{k+1}) = x·re((ix)^k),
-- which solves in closed form along the i-power 4-cycle:
--   re((ix)^{2m})   = (−x²)^m,   im((ix)^{2m})   = 0,
--   re((ix)^{2m+1}) = 0,         im((ix)^{2m+1}) = x·(−x²)^m.
-- These are the real and imaginary parts of the k-th term of exp(ix),
-- and hence (summed) the power series of cosine and sine.

module ComplexNumber.exponential_imaginary

